metadata.name: Grande Dame #45
metadata.description:
Project inspired by the artworks of Vera Molnár ('Grande Dame' of digital art), one of the first women artists to use computers in her practice.

In January month of every year Π will party for Vera birth anniversary, artwork will come alive for the whole month.

Keys to interact:
[c] to change color mode (6 available)
[w] to raise wear level
[1] to [9] to change resolution
[s] to save as png (current settings)
[r] to reset all changes

Also in January:
[p] to pause/play animation
[r] to view standard artwork (paused)

Generative artwork by Gandhiavelli, @gandhiavelli. Made with p5js in 2022.

metadata.name: Orchard #79
metadata.description:
A natural media rendering of a fruit tree during one of the four seasons. Sometimes, you'll catch it at night - with lights strung on the tree!

The amount of color in spring and fall, snow in winter, fruit on and off the tree will all vary. There are four spring bloom palettes, four trunk colors, and seven types of fruit. 

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1000x1000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

To render a variation at a new size, open live view and append '?size=#' to the end of the URL. The new size may be from 100 to 3,000. This version will not be a 1:1 match to your edition but will have all of the same features.

metadata.name: Cubick (Neon Red) #12
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender Renders.

The variations are best viewed in live mode.

In each output, the four "cubes" are arranged in the same calming, 'zen-like' formation.

In each output, the orientation of the "cubes", and the number and positions of the colored regions varies.

All outputs in this collection will have the same color palette (called Neon Red).

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1375x1500px PNG.

Several "Cubick" collections will be released, each with a different color palette.

metadata.name: Gerhard #359
metadata.description:
Gerhard is a collaboration of Richard Nadler and Leander Herzog on fxhash. A generative animation based on multiple layers of color and data, mixed, moved and painted over in realtime. Some fragments stick to the canvas while others get discarded to leave the existing layers visible, allowing a complex surface to emerge and build up over time. 
Richard Nadler created the textures to control composition and color. Leander Herzog created the code for the interplay between the layers, motion and interactions. Both artists use different tools and are not aware of the details of each others process, meeting through the interface of pixels. This collaboration is enabled by twitter and fxhash, as the generative art community continues to explore abstraction in summer 2022 – while extreme temperatures, wildfires, ongoing conflicts and volatile markets continue to escalate. 

- Click to start a new layer of motion and color. 
- Doubleclick to enter fullscreen mode. 
- Press “s” to save the current canvas. 
- Append ?dpr=4 to the url to increase the resolution.

https://leanderherzog.ch/2022/gerhard/

metadata.name: Floatrest #55
metadata.description:
Floating forests over the endless sky, where birds, trees, plants, roots, rocks and waterfalls share an ecosystem full of life and emotion.

You can see some rain clouds in the sky and the sun shining under the raindrops.

The earth is moving, the blocks are falling, but the trees are strong in their roots.

Welcome to 'Floatrest'.

----

# Features

- 7 tree palettes
- 17 different background colors
- 10 different terrain colors
- clouds
- vines
- roots
- plants
- waterfall
- birds
- sun / moon
- night
- dark mode
- monochromatic
- 2 different aspect ratios (square & portrait)
- Press "p" on live mode to save in PNG

This artwork requires processing power and is intended for laptops and desktops primarily. It may take some time to render.

----

July 2022, gpitombo

metadata.name: Happenings #209
metadata.description:
Inspired by the chaos and imperfectly beautiful dynamics of parenting and life, 'Happenings' is the embodiment of the messiness, the unexpected and playful experiences that allow for the greatest depths of connection with our children.

Our intention was to evoke our deepest and most personal feelings as parents of young ones navigating the challenges of the pandemic while immersing ourselves in the Web3 arena.

This collection is Jimena + Marcos’ first generative art collection in the Tezos blockchain via FX Hash, and consists of 222 1/1 artworks created with javascript.

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #644
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.
